Steve,
   That&#39;s an awesome idea.  I&#39;d like to know it would work too because I have a pocket pc laying around here.  I did something a little different this past weekend with the evpm.  I made a 5 minute recording of the sounds and took them on a investigation with me to introduce it to the team.  We didn&#39;t get a chance to use it much but it was great being able to take the sounds along to use when needed.

Bryan

----- Original Message ----
From: &quot;urkel23@...&quot; &lt;urkel23@...&gt;
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
Sent: Tuesday, April 1, 2008 3:05:54 PM
Subject: Re: [EVP-ITC] Seperated voices.


Frank,

The files i heard clearly was the &quot;Frank, i&#39;m talking&quot;and &quot;Thank you, 
princess&quot;.  The other i heard &quot;He&#39;s&quot; and &quot;The Voltage&quot;, but didn&#39;t 
catch the &quot;Checking&quot; part.  All in all, sounds like a &quot;Frank&#39;s Box&quot; to 
me.  Although boxes automate the raw material, i&#39;m finding that other 
methods prove success as well.  Even traditional EVP with my Panasonic 
rr-dr60 is proving to be a positive attribute.  I think once they get in 
touch with your life signature or aura or whatever they see in us, you can use 
any method and get great results.  I have used every box and method known 
and have had success with every one, i keep all my files backed up from this 
journey for future reference.  My problem is that i don&#39;t stay on one style 
of EVP, i keep jumping around to try new things.  I also have another small 
project in the works, an idea i passed by Stefan the other day.  I bought 
an old pocket pc off Ebay that i didn&#39;t get yet.  It is a bit older and has 
a windows CE based program installed on it, Stefan seems to believe that 
EvpMaker might work on that kind of palm pilot because it is a C+++ designed 
program.  Well, in a couple days i will let you guys know if it 
works.  If it does, it could be a handheld unit to bring out on location 
and it has already proved to work great for me and some other researchers 
on here.

-Steve H.




